<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4283] setEmbeddedCP should not exit on error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4283</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;setEmbeddedCP should use &apos;return&apos; instead of &apos;exit&apos; if DERBY_HOME was not set.&lt;br/&gt;
Because this script will be sourced from a shell, use of exit will terminate the calling shell.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>cygwin on windows (bash)</environment>
        <key id="12428488">DERBY-4283</key>
            <summary>setEmbeddedCP should not exit on error</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/minor.png">Minor</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
